<stack-static>
    <statement><p><p>
Form a quadratic equation using the factorisation method:
<me>
{3 x^2+12 x}
</me>
</p>

<p>
<fillin characters="15" name="ans1"/>  
</p></p></statement>
    <solution><p><h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<p>
We start with the expression:
</p>

<p>
<me>
{3 x^2+12 x}
</me>
</p>

<p>
Step 1: Identify the common factor.
</p>

<p>
Both terms contain <m>{3}</m>x.
</p>

<p>
Step 2: Factor out the common factor.
</p>

<p>
<me>
{3 x^2+12 x} = {3}x(x + {4})
</me>
</p>

<p>
Step 3: Form the quadratic equation.
</p>

<p>
<me>
{3}x(x + {4}) = 0
</me>
</p>

<p>
Therefore, the quadratic equation is:
</p>

<p>
<me>
\boxed{{3}x(x + {4}) = 0}
</me>
</p></p></solution>
    <answer><p><m>3 x \left(x+4\right)=0</m></p></answer>
</stack-static>